{"id":"2208.11579","submitter":"Firdavs Rakhmonov","authors":"Firdavs Rakhmonov","title":"Distribution of similar configurations in subsets of $\\mathbb{F}_q^d$","comments":"25 pages, 6 figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.CO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $\\mathbb{F}_q$ be a finite field of order $q$ and $\\mathcal{E}$ be a set\nin $\\mathbb{F}_q^d$. The distance set of $\\mathcal{E}$ is defined as\n$\\Delta(\\mathcal{E}):=\\{\\lVert x-y \\rVert :x,y\\in \\mathcal{E}\\}$, where $\\lVert\nx \\rVert=x_1^2+\\dots+x_d^2$. Iosevich, Koh and Parshall (2018) proved that if\n$d\\geq 2$ is even and $|\\mathcal{E}|\\gg q^{d/2}$, then $$\\mathbb{F}_q=\n\\frac{\\Delta(\\mathcal{E})}{\\Delta(\\mathcal{E})}=\\left\\{\\frac{a}{b}: a\\in\n\\Delta(\\mathcal{E}),\\ b\\in \\Delta(\\mathcal{E})\\setminus\\{0\\} \\right\\}.$$ In\nother words, for each $r\\in \\mathbb{F}_q^{\\times}$ there exist $(x,y)\\in\n\\mathcal{E}^2$ and $(x',y')\\in \\mathcal{E}^2$ such that $\\lVert x-y\\rVert\\neq0$\nand $\\lVert x'-y' \\rVert=r\\lVert x-y\\rVert$.\n  Geometrically, this means that if the size of $\\mathcal{E}$ is large, for any\ngiven $r \\in \\mathbb{F}_q^{\\times}$ we can find a pair of edges in the complete\ngraph $K_{|\\mathcal{E}|}$ with vertex set $\\mathcal{E}$ such that one of them\nis dilated by $r\\in \\mathbb{F}_q^{\\times}$ with respect to the other. A natural\nquestion arises whether it is possible to generalize this result to arbitrary\nsubgraphs of $K_{|\\mathcal{E}|}$ with vertex set $\\mathcal{E}$ and this is the\ngoal of this paper.\n  In this paper, we solve this problem for pair of $k$-paths with $k\\geq 2$,\npair of simplexes and pair of 4-cycles. We are using a mix of tools from\ndifferent areas such as enumerative combinatorics, group actions and Tur\\'an\ntype theorems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 24 Aug 2022 14:32:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-25"}
